					<div class="bio-img-container">
						<div class="bio-img">
							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/zpicMichaelChylinski-100x100.jpeg" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/zpicMichaelChylinski-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Diana Arterian" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Diana Arterian</h4>
												<p>Diana Arterian is the author of the recent poetry collection <em>Agrippina the Younger</em> (Northwestern University Press, 2025). Her first book, <em>Playing Monster :: Seiche</em>, received a starred review in Publishers Weekly and was a Poetry Foundation Staff Pick. A Poetry Editor at Noemi Press, her creative work has been recognized with fellowships from the Banff Centre, Millay Arts, and Yaddo, among others. Diana writes “The Annotated Nightstand” column at Lit Hub and lives in Los Angeles.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
